    "Therefore in addition to charge conservation U (1) C, an approximate U (1) v valley conservation law emerges at low energies.",
    "As we will see, this is promoted to an exact U (1) v in the BM model, leading to a total internal symmetry U (2) K × U (2) K ′ ≃ SU (2) K × SU (2) K ′ × U (1) C × U (1) v upon the inclusion of spin (recall that the intrinsic spin-orbit coupling is very weak in graphene [120][121][122][123][124][125][126]).The above discussion implicitly assumed a rigid rotation of layers.",
    "However, a real twisted graphene bilayer may stretch and deform to minimize the combination of elastic and interlayer potential energies.",
    "In fact, without doing an explicit moiré calculation, we can already qualitatively anticipate the form of such relaxation.",
    "In rigidly-twisted TBG, we can identify regions where the local stacking configuration is AA or AB, as shown in Fig. 2."
